A convention bureau at the KICC will help reform the conferencing sector, CEO Nana Gecaga has said. The bureau has been set up to provide information on conference tourism to increase bookings and events. Gecaga was a key speaker at the Imex Policy Forum in Frankfurt held in collaboration with United Nations World Tourism Organisation. Participants discussed legacy of positive policy making to explore how to bridge the partnership gap between national, local governments and the meetings industry. Other panellistsÂ were Justice Thomas Mihayo, chairman Tanzania Tourist Board and deputy Tourism minister South Africa Elizabeth Thabethe.